main event: An unidentified object was sighted in Winchester, Massachusetts on July 2, 1956.
interesting points: The object was yellow-white in color and its shape was not discernible.
The object was moving in a very light circle when first observed.
After completing four 90-degree turns, the object proceeded in a NNW direction.
The speed of the object when on a straight course was estimated at 700 mph.
The report mentions a similar sighting in Conway, Massachusetts on the same day, where the object was able to reverse its course completely and had a low-pitched hum.
